The Federal Medical Centre, Ebute Metta, Lagos, on Monday urged the public to disregard on-going fraudulent messages about recruitment in the hospital circulating in the social media. Its Head of Corporate Services, Dr Ayoola Olorunfemi, stated that the hospital did not engage any recruitment agent or consultant, and did not authorise any announcement of recruitment. “This is to inform Nigerians of the fraudulent activity of Interns-Connect.ng 40 Group created by some individuals to defraud the public on social media platforms regarding recruitment in the hospital. “The management hereby wishes to inform the general public that the hospital has no recruitment agent or consultant. “The advert going viral in the social media, especially on WhatsApp platform is meant to defraud the public and should be disregarded,’’ he stated 